= <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> Party Vote

The non-industrialist and Stresemannite elements of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> have revolted, angered by their marginalization at the hands of the industrialists, who have pushed to realign Stresemann’s former party with the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">national</span> <span style="color: #3E88B3;">opposition</span>.

Led by Wilhelm Kunz, a Berlin lawyer, and Count Alexander zu Dohna, a legal expert and widely respected figure on the party’s left wing, they aim to publicly challenge Dingeldey and the industrialist faction that has effectively puppeteered him.

They both advocate for cooperation with the minor bourgeois parties and the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>, and firmly reject what they call the “psychosis of <span style="color: #7A3C00;">National Socialism</span>.”

